  m_text: Wheat is a cereal grain that is one of the most widely cultivated staple
    crops in the world. It grows on tall grass-like plants that produce heads filled
    with small, edible kernels called wheat grains. These plants thrive in temperate
    climates and are typically grown in large fields where they can be harvested
    efficiently. Wheat is rich in carbohydrates and provides important nutrients
    such as fiber, protein, and several B vitamins, making it a key source of energy
    in many diets. After harvesting, wheat is processed into flour, which is used
    to make a wide variety of foods including bread, pasta, cereals, and baked goods.
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
