      m_Calls: []
  m_text: White mushrooms, also known as button mushrooms, are one of the most commonly
    consumed edible fungi in the world. They have smooth, rounded white caps, short
    stems, and pinkish to dark brown gills underneath the cap where spores are produced.
    These mushrooms grow in rich, moist environments and are typically harvested
    while still young and small, which gives them their mild flavor and tender texture.
    White mushrooms are low in calories but contain important nutrients such as B
    vitamins, selenium, and antioxidants that support overall health. They are highly
    versatile in cooking and can be eaten raw or cooked in dishes like salads, soups,
    stir-fries, and sauces.
