      m_Calls: []
  m_text: Red peppers, often known as red bell peppers, are vibrant, sweet vegetables
    that develop from green peppers as they fully ripen on the plant. They have a
    smooth, glossy skin and a hollow interior divided into sections that contain
    small white seeds. Compared to their unripe green counterparts, red peppers are
    sweeter and have a more complex, slightly fruity flavor. They are rich in nutrients,
    especially vitamin C, vitamin A, and antioxidants, which support immune health
    and overall wellness. Red peppers grow best in warm, sunny conditions and are
    commonly used in a wide range of dishes, including salads, stir-fries, roasted
    vegetable mixes, and stuffed pepper recipes.
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
