      m_Calls: []
  m_text: Sunflowers are tall, striking plants known for their large, bright yellow
    flower heads that resemble the sun. They can grow several feet high, with thick,
    sturdy stems and broad, rough-textured green leaves. The flower head is made
    up of many tiny individual florets, with the outer petals radiating around a
    central disk that produces seeds. Sunflowers naturally turn to face the sun as
    they grow, a behavior called heliotropism. They thrive in full sunlight and well-drained
    soil, making them popular in gardens and agricultural fields. Sunflowers are
    valued not only for their beauty but also for their seeds, which can be eaten
    as a snack or pressed to produce sunflower oil.
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2180264, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
